products.title: Mini M416 Gel Blaster with Double Mag & Battery C
products.body_html:
Mini M416 Gel Blaster with Double Mag  &  Battery

Mini M416 Gel Blaster: Safe, Exciting, and Perfect for Young Gel Blasters!

Get ready for a thrilling gel blasting experience designed specifically for kids with the Mini M416 Gel Blaster. This exciting blaster combines the iconic M416 design with child-friendly features, ensuring a safe and enjoyable adventure for young gel blasting enthusiasts.

The Mini M416 Gel Blaster is crafted with safety as a top priority. It uses a low-impact gel ball ammunition that provides a fun shooting experience without causing harm or discomfort. The gel balls are soft and dissolve when soaked in water, making them safe for outdoor play.

Designed to be lightweight and easy to handle, the Mini M416 Gel Blaster is perfectly suited for kids' hands. Its compact size allows for easy maneuverability, making it ideal for quick tactical moves during friendly battles. The top hopper feeding mechanism enables easy and convenient loading, so kids can quickly reload and get back into the action.

To ensure extended playtime, the Mini M416 Gel Blaster comes with a rechargeable battery that provides hours of continuous fun. Simply charge the battery and let the adventure begin. The battery is easy to use and safe for kids, providing a hassle-free gel blasting experience.

The Mini M416 Gel Blaster features a simple and intuitive firing mechanism, allowing kids to easily operate the blaster. The semi-automatic firing mode offers a thrilling burst of gel balls with each trigger pull, enhancing the excitement of battles and encouraging active play.

Parents can have peace of mind knowing that the Mini M416 Gel Blaster is made from high-quality materials, ensuring durability and longevity. It is built to withstand energetic play, making it a reliable companion for countless gel blasting adventures.

Engage your young adventurers with the Mini M416 Gel Blaster, providing them with a safe and thrilling gel blasting experience. Let their imaginations soar as they create epic battles, hone their strategic skills, and have endless hours of fun with friends and family.

Note: Adult supervision is recommended when children are using gel blasters. Always follow local regulations and guidelines regarding the use of gel blasters in your area.

Equip your young gel blasters with the Mini M416 Gel Blaster and watch them embark on exciting missions. Spark their enthusiasm for outdoor play, promote teamwork, and create unforgettable memories. With its top hopper feeding system for easy loading, the Mini M416 Gel Blaster ensures that the fun never stops. Get ready for endless fun and laughter with the Mini M416 Gel Blaster designed specifically for kids!

products.title: V2 Ultra Elite Gels
products.body_html:
Ultra Elite V2 gels are the latest hardened gel ball formula, on offer from Ausgel.

These gels are perfect for:

  • High-powered AEG gel blasters,
  • Gas Blowback gel blaster pistols (CO2 or green gas),
  • Gas Blowback gel blaster rifles,
  • HPA Blasters (with tuning), and
  • High-powered spring gel blasters, such as sniper rifles.

What makes these gels so special?


These gels can be stored in water.
Consistent grow results when left in water for 12+ hours. Check out the review video by
Bradley Phillips on YouTube where he achieved good results after a 48 hour grow!
Very strong gels (7-8kg crush pressure as seen during the Low Guido You Tube review).
Dry gels to not have a strange alcoholic odour, which has been common of this type of
gel in the past.


Grow data:
4 Hours for 7.1 – 7.4mm gels*
9 Hours for 7.2 – 7.4mm gels*
12+ Hours for 7.3mm gels (best results)*
* These grow times are based on results of feedback from a wide range of
customers. Grow time may vary slightly, so always test a smaller sample from your
bag before committing to a specific grow time.
Average weight: .20g (weight can vary with water supply and can be heavier).
Crush weight: 7-8kg.

GUIDE – AUSGEL ULTRA ELITE V2


Step 1: Using a waterproof container, add CLEAN water then pour in dry gels as follows:
• 1 cup of water for 1 teaspoon of gels, or *
• 2 cups of water for 1 tablespoon of gels, or *
• 2 litres of water for 1 packet of gels. *
Step 2: Allow gels to grow as per below:
• 4 Hours for 7.1 – 7.4mm gels*
• 9 Hours for 7.2 – 7.4mm gels*
• 12+ Hours for 7.3mm gels (best results)*
* These grow times are based on results of feedback from a wide range of customers.
Grow time may vary slightly, so always test a smaller sample from your bag before
committing to a specific grow time.
* Keep in mind, there is no right or wrong answer as to how much water is required to grow your
gels other than: the gels must remain submerged during the grow process.
* Your grow time and results may vary dramatically depending on various environmental factors
such as:
Your water source (local catchment / dam)
Temperature of your water
Your local climate (northern tropics, air-conditioned room, refrigerator etc)
Your grow container (the wider the better). Narrow containers, such as soft drink bottles,
can lead to deformities due to pressure from the gels at the top of your grow batch
weighing down on the gels at the bottom of your bottle during the grow. A large bucket or
sealable deep-dish tray is perfect.
TIPS
Once gels are removed from water, don’t dry them out completely. A quick shake off in a
sieve is fine. It is ok for your gels to be a little bit wet for the purpose of lubrication.
Once you have finished a gel ball session, it is recommended that you store your gels in
water, within a sealed container. If left out of water for 1 hour or longer, the gels can start
to shrink which will affect size consistency and shape. If the gels are left out of water for
too long, this will affect accuracy and feeding.
Don’t freeze your gels. This will not make them harder but will instead cause them to
become more brittle.
Ultra Elite V2 gel balls can be left in water for up to 3 weeks, maintaining shape, strength
and consistency. *They can potentially be stored in water for longer, however this has not
yet been tested.
Water supply can affect your grow. It is strongly recommended that you utilise the
cleanest water available to you. Avoid storm water. Clean tap water, bottled water or
distilled water is fine. Using any chemical or liquid other than water to grow your gel balls
will be at your own risk and is not recommended.
For best results, grow your gels in distilled water, chilled (in your refrigerator – not
freezer) within a sealed container. Chilled water will typically lead to a longer grow time,
but results in more consistent and stronger gels.

If using an electronic gel sorter, please note: these devices generally need to be tuned to
ensure the resulting assortment is accurate. Always ensure you double check gel size
with a quality set of vernier callipers to ensure your sorter is performing accurately.

products.title: Prometheus V2 EG Gearbox
products.body_html:
The Prometheus EG Hard 8mm Gearbox by LayLax is a high-quality and innovative gearbox, perfect as a centrepiece for most AEG builds. This gearbox is aimed at users who want to build a reliable and highly efficient AEG Gel Blaster, with significant quality-of-life inclusions, to make the initial build process and future maintenance more enjoyable. Featuring a split-panel design, this gearbox shell will streamline the build process of your AEG Gel Blaster with the following inclusions:

 

  • External wiring channels, reducing likelihood of gear/wire contact while creating more space within the gearbox
  • Pre-radiused cuts around the cylinder window to reduce operational gearbox stress
  • Easy shimming and AOE correction due to the split-panel system
  • High quality M3 steel screws
  • Compatibility with 8mm bushings/bearings
  • Precision machined aluminium gearbox panel and high strength cast zinc alloy main body
  • A spring retainer, perfectly fitted for this gearbox
  • Designed by Japanese Engineers

 

Tolerances:

 

  • Spring: M120
  • 350 FPS

 

Caution:

  • Metal parts require periodic lubrication – always stay on top of maintenance!
  • If you have limited technical experience, it is recommended you consult a gel blaster technician (service available at most gel blaster retail stores)
  • Do not exceed tolerances – this gearbox is designed for reliability and sustainable use, not for extreme FPS/RPS builds

products.title: V3 Mosfet with wiring
products.body_html:
Professionally made mosfet designed for AEG Gel Blasters that use Version 3-style gearboxes (usually found in AK models - consult with the manufacturer of your blaster to confirm compatibility).
This device increases your rate of fire and improves battery life.
It is fully integratable inside version 3 gearboxes as an alternative to the original trigger contacts, compatible with Tokyo Marui standard.

SPECIFICATIONS:
- Mosfet built on trigger contacts from SHS
- Easy installation for Version 3 gearboxes
- Presoldered wires allow faster and easier installation into your blaster, long enough for all kind of V3 gearbox blasters. Simply cut wires to the required length and attach connectors (included in package)
- Contains presoldered high quality: 2 black wires 1.5 qmm (AWG16) with MPPE insulation, length 400 mm to the motor and 600 mm to the battery. The blue wire is 0.34 qmm (AWG22) with a length of 1000 mm and is used for connection anywhere on the red wire
- Included: 1000 mm red wire 1.5qmm (AWG16) with MPPE insulation
- Board covered by conformal coating, to protect device against water
- Designed for spring sizes up to M160 (equivalent for current 75A single shot fire or 25A burst fire for max. 30s). 
- Specified for common batteries up to 17V (Ni-xx 8.4 - 12V, lipol 7.4 - 14.8V)
- No current consumption in the idle mode
- No sparking on switch contacts
- In auto fire mode, the piston will stop in a random position due to the mechanical box design on V3 blasters
- To function correctly, it is necessary to have a functional gearbox cut off lever, selector plate, reverse latch, trigger and trigger block, as it has the standard gearbox

INSTALLATION FOR THIS DEVICE IS INTENDED FOR EXPERIENCED TECHS ONLY. THERE IS CONFORMAL COATING ON THIS PCB - IF YOU ATTEMPT TO HOLD A SOLDERING IRON TO THIS BOARD WITHOUT FIRST REMOVING THE COATING, YOU WILL DAMAGE THE BOARD AND VOID YOUR WARRANTY

DEVICE INSTRUCTIONS: you can download installation manual in English here [PDF, 761.42 kB]
PACKING: 
- mosfet on trigger contacts with wiring
- trigger switch
- DeanT connector male
- 30A mini fuse
- 4x faston female 2,8mm
- 6x black heat shrink tube 3,2mm - length 20mm
- 3x black heat shrink tube 4,8mm - length 20mm
- Installation manual in English

WARNING: JeffTron advises that installation of this device should be left to experts, who can solder and disassemble gel blasters. Never user soldering gun! Visit your closest tech for installation support.
We can't guarantee 100% compatibility with all gearboxes, but this V3 mosfet will fit into standard and common brand's V3 gearboxes without extensive modifications.

With a minimum loss in power and consistency, the Mil-Spec spring series is the ULTIMATE choice for your AEG Gel Blaster. The Mil-Spec springs are color coded for better identifying them when switching out the spring for different skirmishes.

The springs are designed from the start to deliver the best output while keeping it's coil strength, consistancy, and quality. With the closed and ground ends, the spring remains in place during use to prevent a reduction in ROF due to bending.

WARNING: Do not attempt to install this product unless experienced. Incorrect installation can damage your gel blaster - it is recommended that you utilise an industry technician to assist in the installation of this product to ensure you have compatible blaster parts that will support this spring

Compatibility: Most popular Gel Blaster AEG Platforms
Material: Spring Steel

products.title: White Pearls Gels 7-8mm
products.body_html:
White Pearl gels are the strongest 'milky white' currently available on the market. Compatible with Gas Blowback and HPA blasters running a 7.5mm barrel, these gels are very easy to trace and perfect for competitive gel ballers want to see where they are shooting.

Slightly harder than a standard Armour Tech White gel, slightly softer than an Armour Tech Ultra gel - these gels will be excepted for use at most casual venues.

For best results, use within 48 hours and in gel blasters <300 fps.

GROW INSTRUCTIONS

Step 1: Pour at least 2 litres of CLEAN water into your grow container, then add 1 packet of Armour Tech White Pearl gels (in dry form).

 

Step 2: Allow gels to grow as per below:

 

• 1 hour - for 6mm sized gels
• 1.5 hours for 6.9 - 7.1mm sized gels.
• 3.5 hours for 7.2 - 7.5mm sized gels.
(RECOMMENDED)

Step 3: Remove gels from water – they are now ready to use in your gel blaster.

Notes: If using in a CO2 Blaster, white pearls should be used within 48 hours. White pearls that have been grown for 3 hours or less, should be stored in an airtight container. Gels grown for 3.5 hours or more can be stored in water, but will swell to 7.5-7.6mm and lose some strength, so it is recommended to grow the White Pearl gels for same or next day use.

Recommended Barrel Size: 7.5mm Inner Diameter (3.5 hour grow)

products.title: MAC-11/G12 Gel Blaster
products.body_html:
Well Mac-11 Gel Blaster

The pocket A-10, the BRRRRRRTT brick… whatever you want to call it, the ultimate pistol/SMG has arrived!

The Ingram Mac11 is a subcompact machine pistol/submachine developed by American gun designer Gordon Ingram at the Military Armament Corporation (MAC) during the 1970s.

 

Suppressor

The Mac-11 has a 14mm counter-clockwise thread for fitting your suppressor, an alloy barrel and a front sling/grip mount.

Full Metal

Full metal body, and gears, this blaster is ready for action. And with that, comes an incredible rate of fire hitting 30-36 rps at 180-240 FPS.

C02 Power

To keep up with that rate of fire, the Mac-11 is CO2 powered, with the C02 bulb going into the bottom of the magazine. With great power comes great responsibility, never dry fire your Mac-11, never slam the mag in with the bolt closed, and keep up your maintenance.

M4A1 recommends upgrading your gels to some Ausgel gels for better performance.

 

 

 

 

 

Please remember to check all local laws regarding the usage and ownership of gel blasters in your particular State or Territory.

Gelblasters must be concealed during transport and used in designated areas.

Features
  • Full Metal Construction
  • 14mm CCW outer barrel for attaching Suppressors, Hopups or Tracer Units
  • Retractable stock
  • Large Capacity CO2 magazine
  • 180-240FPS depending on gels, gas pressure and temperature
  • 30-36RPS, we struggled to get an exact ROF because the MAC11 is simply too awesome for the Chrono we used to test it with!!!

Package Includes

C Rating: 16C (equivalent of a 1600mAh 30C)

Is this enough? Why C rating is only half the equation.

 

Size: 19.5mm (0.77in) thick, 132mm (5.2in) long

Learn how to charge a Titan Pack on YouTube

 

No Puff

Titan Power batteries will never puff and become unsafe, like lipos will that have been either neglected or simply aged over time.

 

No Memory

Titan Power batteries can be charged from empty or nearly full without damaging the battery. Even if your battery gets low and your device cannot cycle, the battery is still within safe operating ranges and can be charged safely back to 100%.

 

More Power

Beginning in 2020, the Titan Power product line outperforms ALL gel blaster batteries, with the same or higher rate of fire, and the same or greater trigger response, when comparing like voltage and similar size.

 

More Capacity

Titan Power batteries can store on average 2-5 times the energy of other gel blaster batteries, keeping you in the game longer.

 

No Fade / Lasts Forever

Titan Power batteries can hold a charge for months and still be ready to use on game day. An extreme example is a pack used for testing, charged in 2012, which still holds 88% of its life in 2018. These packs can also be charged over 300 times and still store 80% of its original capacity.

 

Warrantied and Guaranteed

Titan Power will beat your old battery, or your money back. Product claims sound too good to be true? Titan Power is the only company that backs all gel blaster products with a 1 year warranty.

 

The only gel blaster battery made in the USA with a one year warranty. Titan Power packs have the performance, high capacity, and reliability needed to make your battery a part of your kit- not a consumable. Patriotically rapid innovation with strict quality assurance bring gel ball players a power solution that needs very little attention to maintain a long life of use. The American team of owners, engineers, and production employees love skirmish sports, and hope that passion shines brightly through each product.

products.body_html:
Mini M416 Gel Blaster with Double Mag  &  Battery

Mini M416 Gel Blaster: Safe, Exciting, and Perfect for Young Gel Blasters!

Get ready for a thrilling gel blasting experience designed specifically for kids with the Mini M416 Gel Blaster. This exciting blaster combines the iconic M416 design with child-friendly features, ensuring a safe and enjoyable adventure for young gel blasting enthusiasts.

The Mini M416 Gel Blaster is crafted with safety as a top priority. It uses a low-impact gel ball ammunition that provides a fun shooting experience without causing harm or discomfort. The gel balls are soft and dissolve when soaked in water, making them safe for outdoor play.

Designed to be lightweight and easy to handle, the Mini M416 Gel Blaster is perfectly suited for kids' hands. Its compact size allows for easy maneuverability, making it ideal for quick tactical moves during friendly battles. The top hopper feeding mechanism enables easy and convenient loading, so kids can quickly reload and get back into the action.

To ensure extended playtime, the Mini M416 Gel Blaster comes with a rechargeable battery that provides hours of continuous fun. Simply charge the battery and let the adventure begin. The battery is easy to use and safe for kids, providing a hassle-free gel blasting experience.

The Mini M416 Gel Blaster features a simple and intuitive firing mechanism, allowing kids to easily operate the blaster. The semi-automatic firing mode offers a thrilling burst of gel balls with each trigger pull, enhancing the excitement of battles and encouraging active play.

Parents can have peace of mind knowing that the Mini M416 Gel Blaster is made from high-quality materials, ensuring durability and longevity. It is built to withstand energetic play, making it a reliable companion for countless gel blasting adventures.

Engage your young adventurers with the Mini M416 Gel Blaster, providing them with a safe and thrilling gel blasting experience. Let their imaginations soar as they create epic battles, hone their strategic skills, and have endless hours of fun with friends and family.

Deluxe - Orange

Suitable for 7-8 mm Gel Blasters

Work best in 7.5 mm ID Barrels

Deluxe Hardened Orange are the toughest of the deluxe range and comparable to ‘Hardened Orange’ gels previously sold at Ausgel. This colour tends to work well in SKD gel blasters and all 7-8 mm gel pistols.

To grow:

  1. Add 2 cups of water to every 1 teaspoon of dry gels
  2. Wait 4 hours
  3. Remove from water. Gels are ready to use in your blaster!

To store:

  • Keep in an airtight container for up to 3 months
  • Do not store near heat sources or in direct sunlight
  • Store submerged in water for up to 1 year

products.title: Well M4 Metal CQB Blaster
products.body_html:
Well M4 Metal CQB Blaster

This Blaster is designed for Close Quarter Combat (CQC) or Close Quarter Battle (CQB). The size and shape is well loved by gel baller's who like to duck around tight fields. This gel blaster comes with the classic M4 shape and a sleek battle look. The Close Quarter Battle (CQB) unit continues the Well M4 evolution and brings a full metal build that will leave you in awe. It comes with the 11.1-volt mini tamiya battery.

 

The Perfect CQB Blaster

The short alloy barrel brings a great look that comes with flip up/down metal "iron sights". Perfect for any CQB field both indoors and outdoors. Add a torch to one of the picatinny rail's add it's sleek black finishing and you are ready to win the your next battle.

I Might Be Small, But I Pack A Punch

The Metal Well CQB has the strong and powerful metal gearbox and gears we all know and love. Right out of the box you get the 480 long-high speed motor with the 18:1 metal gears and a 11.1 volt battery in a full metal receiver. All this helps it hit the 280 - 290 FPS.

Ready For Battle

This blaster is ready to go with everything you need straight out of the box. Hit your closest CQB Field on the way home.

products.title: DELUXE - GREEN
products.body_html:
Deluxe - Green

Suitable for 7-8 mm Gel Blasters

Work best in 7.5 mm ID Barrels

Deluxe Hardened Green are best for new players who want to approach skirmish games in a stealth manner. They are comparable to ‘Hardened Green’ gels previously sold at Ausgel. This colour is very hard to see against vegetation, meaning your enemies will have a hard time seeing where the gels are being fired from!

To grow:

  1. Add 2 cups of water to every 1 teaspoon of dry gels
  2. Wait 4 hours
  3. Remove from water. Gels are ready to use in your blaster!

To store:

  • Keep in an airtight container for up to 3 months
  • Do not store near heat sources or in direct sunlight
  • Store submerged in water for up to 1 year

products.body_html:
ARMOUR TECH YELLOWS

Average Size: 7.26 mm

Average Weight: 0.21 g

Crush Threshold (distance gel can be squeezed before breaking): 2.80 mm

Barrel compatibility: 7.2 - 7.5 mm

Batch: AG001

Armour Tech Yellows are the heavy gel formula that is building a reputation for hardness and strength. Players who have been on the receiving end of a gel blaster using Armour Tech Yellows will know when they've been marked! This batch is not available anywhere else, as Ausgel purchased the entire batch once it was manufactured.

The Armour Tech range has been well-received by the Gel Ball community as one of the best gel ball ranges available to date. Get yours today and find out why!

To grow:

  1. Add 2.5 cups of water to every 1 teaspoon of dry gels
  2. Wait 4 hours
  3. Remove from water. Gels are ready to use in your blaster!

To store:

  • Keep in an airtight container for up to 3 months
  • Do not store near heat sources or in direct sunlight
  • The Armour Tech range can be stored in water for up to 1 year but will lose some hardness (they will still work fine through your blaster)

FOR BEST RESULTS AND PERFORMANCE, ONLY GROW THE AMOUNT OF GELS YOU INTEND TO USE IMMEDIATELY
